  "body": "### User Story\nAs a user, I want to have autofocus on some input fields, so I don't waste time clicking on them in order to write something.\n\n### Description\n*Type*: Bug\n\n*Summary*: Let's implement auto-focus :)\n\n#### Expected behavior\nWhen accessing a screen or component in which the main action is to write something, let's implement auto-focus on the input field, with the cursor blinking and ready to write something. \n\n#### Actual behavior\nE.g. When accessing a chat, the cursor is not on the message area. So, the user needs to spend extra energy clicking on the input field to start writing.\n\n<img width=\"1029\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-09-12 a la s 1 55 13 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/45423454-af29cc80-b693-11e8-881d-559a4b467cbf.png\">\n\n### Solution\nAuto-focus to be implemented in the following cases:\n- When opening a chat > focus on \"Type a message\" input field\n- When signing in > focus on password\n- When creating a new account > focus on password (step1), then on confirm (step2) and then on name (step3).\n- When recovering an account > focus on Recovery phrase, and then -on tab- focus on password.\n\n### Additional\nFor a \"happy form-filling experience\", see also #4728 and #5548",
